# Data Fetching Patterns

## The API client

File: `apps/backoffice-web/src/lib/erp-api.ts`

```ts
import { erpApi, requireErpData, requireErpSuccess } from "../lib/erp-api";
```

`erpApi` is a typed client built from the OpenAPI spec (`@erp/api-client`).
It injects `Authorization`, `X-Branch-Id`, `X-Request-Id`, and `X-Idempotency-Key` headers automatically.

### Reading data

```ts
// requireErpData — throws HttpError on API error, returns T on success
const data = requireErpData(
  await erpApi.GET("/inventory/items", {
    params: { query: { page: 1, pageSize: 20 } },
  })
);
```

### Mutating data (create / update / delete)

```ts
// requireErpSuccess — throws on error, returns void (for operations with no body)
requireErpSuccess(
  await erpApi.DELETE("/inventory/items/{id}", {
    params: { path: { id: itemId } },
  })
);

// requireErpData — for mutations that return a body
const created = requireErpData(
  await erpApi.POST("/inventory/items", { body: dto })
);
```

