## Generic CRUD hooks (admin entity platform)

The backoffice has pre-built hooks for any entity registered in the CrudModule:

```ts
import {
  useCrudConfig,
  useCrudRecords,
  useCrudCreate,
  useCrudUpdate,
  useCrudDelete,
} from "../components/crud/useCrudApi";

// entity key = the entityKey registered on the server (e.g. "inventory-items")
const { data: config } = useCrudConfig("inventory-items");
const { data, isLoading } = useCrudRecords("inventory-items", { page, pageSize: 20, search });
const { mutate: create } = useCrudCreate("inventory-items");
const { mutate: update } = useCrudUpdate("inventory-items");
const { mutate: remove } = useCrudDelete("inventory-items");
```

Use `CrudListPage` (at `/admin/:entityKey`) for basic table views — no custom page needed.

